<div class='comments-comment__content'>
<div class='s-marginBottom0_5 u-displayFlex'>
<span class="js-tooltip_ajax  " data-type="user" data-slug="john-saputo-1"><div class="c-avatar c-avatar--small comments-comment__avatar js-user_avatar"><img alt="Profile picture of John Saputo" title="John Saputo" srcset="https://uploads.republic.com/p/users/avatars/small_2x/000/693/256/693256-1595845564-b263c7b62874c4e2d982fc72017822475c1ca767.jpg 2x" src="https://uploads.republic.com/p/users/avatars/small/000/693/256/693256-1595845564-cf28790ecfa3088367c8eda329b2f9cefc9763c0.jpg" /></div>
</span><div class='u-flex1 s-paddingLeft1 u-text-left'>
<div class='u-fontWeight600 comments-comment__name'>
<span class="js-tooltip_ajax u-colorGray3 c-link--no-underline " data-type="user" data-slug="john-saputo-1">John Saputo</span>
</div>
<div class='u-colorGray9'>
<div class='u-colorGray9 u-fontWeight400 s-fontSize12 u-displayInlineBlock u-verticalAlignMiddle'>
over 2 years ago
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='u-fontWeight400 s-marginTop0_5 comments-comment__message'>
I sense that electronic gaming has its own nation and language.   There is a global interest in gaming and the development of new games that challange the devotee. Fig is one of the leaders of this industry.  How can I invest in FIG itself rather than invest in one particular game?  I would rather invest in the brains of the operation who is behind the creation of the new games.  Does that make any sense to you?
</div>
</div>
