<div class='u-colorGray9'>
<div class='u-colorGray9 u-fontWeight400 s-fontSize12 u-displayInlineBlock u-verticalAlignMiddle'>
about 3 years ago
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='u-fontWeight400 s-marginTop0_5 comments-comment__message comments-comment__message--truncated js-show_full_message'>
Although Pong(1972) wasn't the first computer game (it were games like OXO(1952), Tennis for Two(1958) and Spacewar!(1962)), but Pong was the first popular video game in the world.<br>Then there is the incredible first video game console called Magnavox Odyssey(1972).<br>About 60 years later, the movie 'Ready Player One'(2018) showed us the most impressive possibility of future game development and -perception. Will that be the end of the development or what will come afterwards?<br>Video games will change all areas of our social life massively and Andreessen Horowitz described it perfectly with words like 'tectonic shift' + 'transition'.<br>In the end, video games will offer a transformation to everyone regardless of their background and wealth and new pure digital communities will be created.<br>Happy gaming!
</div>
</div>
